Write a program to read n numbers and display the numbers in reverse order
Input:
5
10 20 30 40 50
Output:
50 40 30 20 10
For exam pie:
Input
5
10 20 30 40 50
Result
50 
40 
30 
20 
10


Solution : 
// Java 
import java.util.*;

public class RevOrder {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner a = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        // Read the number of elements
        int b = a.nextInt();
        
        // Declare an array to store the elements
        int[] arr = new int[b];
        
        // Read the elements
        for (int i = 0; i < b; i++) {
            arr[i] = a.nextInt();
        }
        
        // Print the elements in reverse order
        for (int i = arr.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            System.out.println(arr[i]);
        }
    }
}
